---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
---

<PageLayout
  title="Terms of Service — 1404"
  description="Terms of use for 1404 Mission Control and related services."
>
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 pt-40 pb-24">
    <h1 class="font-display text-4xl md:text-5xl text-text-primary mb-4">Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="text-text-muted text-sm mb-12">Last updated: April 9, 2026</p>

    <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none space-y-8 text-text-secondary">

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl text-text-primary font-display mb-3">1. Agreement</h2>
        <p>
          These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your use of Mission Control, a SaaS
          platform provided by 1404 LLC ("1404"). By creating an account or using the
          service, you agree to these Terms.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl text-text-primary font-display mb-3">2. The service</h2>
        <p>
          Mission Control is an AI assistant platform for owner-operated companies.
          1404 hosts the software, provides support, and integrates with third-party
          services (QuickBooks Online, Microsoft 365, Google Workspace) as authorized
          by the customer.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl text-text-primary font-display mb-3">3. Your account</h2>
        <p>
          You are responsible for keeping your login credentials secure and for the
          activity of every user you create on your tenant. Notify 1404 immediately of
          any unauthorized access. Administrators are responsible for inviting and
          removing their own users.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl text-text-primary font-display mb-3">4. Your data</h2>
        <p>
          You retain ownership of all content you submit. You grant 1404 a limited
          license to host, process, and display your content solely for the purpose of
          operating the service on your behalf. See our
          <a href="/privacy" class="text-copper hover:underline">Privacy Policy</a>
          for details on collection, storage, and deletion.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl text-text-primary font-display mb-3">5. Third-party integrations</h2>
        <p>
          When you connect a third-party integration, you authorize 1404 to access the
          scopes you grant during the OAuth consent flow. You can revoke access at any
          time from your integrations page or from the third-party provider directly.
          1404 is not responsible for changes to third-party terms, APIs, or pricing.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl text-text-primary font-display mb-3">6. Acceptable use</h2>
        <p>You agree not to:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
          <li>Use the service for illegal activity</li>
          <li>Reverse engineer, decompile, or attempt to extract source code</li>
          <li>Upload malware, exploit code, or content that violates others' rights</li>
          <li>Use the service to send unsolicited commercial messages</li>
          <li>Resell access to the service without written permission</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl text-text-primary font-display mb-3">7. Fees and billing</h2>
        <p>
          Fees are set out in your signed service agreement or order form. Unless
          otherwise agreed, subscriptions are billed monthly in advance. Late payments
          accrue interest at 1.5% per month. 1404 may suspend access for accounts more
          than 30 days past due.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl text-text-primary font-display mb-3">8. Termination</h2>
        <p>
          Either party may terminate with 30 days written notice. On termination, 1404
          provides a 30-day data export window, then permanently deletes your data per
          the Privacy Policy. Fees paid are non-refundable except as required by law.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl text-text-primary font-display mb-3">9. Warranties and disclaimers</h2>
        <p>
          1404 provides the service "as is" and does not warrant that the service will
          be uninterrupted or error-free. AI outputs are generated probabilistically and
          may contain errors — you are responsible for verifying any output before
          acting on it, especially for financial, legal, or operational decisions.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl text-text-primary font-display mb-3">10. Limitation of liability</h2>
        <p>
          To the maximum extent permitted by law, 1404's aggregate liability is capped
          at the fees you paid in the 12 months preceding the claim. 1404 is not liable
          for indirect, incidental, or consequential damages.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl text-text-primary font-display mb-3">11. Governing law</h2>
        <p>
          These Terms are governed by the laws of the State of Michigan, United States.
          Disputes will be resolved in the state or federal courts located in Washtenaw
          County, Michigan.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl text-text-primary font-display mb-3">12. Changes</h2>
        <p>
          1404 may update these Terms by posting a revised version at
          <a href="/terms" class="text-copper hover:underline">1404.io/terms</a>
          and notifying account owners via email at least 14 days before the change
          takes effect.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl text-text-primary font-display mb-3">Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions:
          <a href="mailto:holden@1404.io" class="text-copper hover:underline">holden@1404.io</a>
          <br />1404 LLC, Ann Arbor, MI
        </p>
      </section>

    </div>
  </section>
</PageLayout>
